#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ventoy will be useful if you can't sucessfully boot the YunoHost image using the other methods.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Ventoy](https://www.ventoy.net/) is a nice tool that makes it really easy to put multiple linux images on a USB stick. When the computer refuses to boot from an image on a USB stick, Ventoy will usually be able to boot it anyway!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. Install [Ventoy](https://www.ventoy.net/) on the USB stick. Refer to the [install instructions](https://www.ventoy.net/en/doc_start.html).\n"
"    - This will create 2 partitions on the stick.\n"
"2. Using your favorite file explorer app, copy the YunoHost image file on the big `Ventoy` partition (not \"VTOYEFI\")\n"
"    - Don't use *Balena Etcher*, USBImager or `dd` for this!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "Later, when you'll boot the computer using this USB stick, Ventoy will appear and will list the images on the USB stick. Select the YunoHost image, then select GRUB2 launch option (or use whichever works for your computer ðŸ˜‰)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "<FAIcon icon=\"fa-plug\"/> Boot the machine on your USB stick"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- Connect your computer to your home router via Ethernet\n"
"- Boot up your server with the USB stick or a CD-ROM inserted, and select it as **bootable device**.\n"
"  - Depending on your hardware, you will need to press one of the following keys:\n"
"`<F9>`, `<F10>`, `<F11>`, `<F12>`, `<DEL>`, `<ESC>` or `<Alt>`.\n"
"  - N.B. : if the server was previously installed with a recent version of Windows (8+), you first need to tell Windows, to \"actually reboot\". This can be done somewhere in \"Advanced startup options\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (tip)
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/regular_computer.mdx:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you can't boot the YunoHost image, try using Ventoy (select \"Ventoy\" in the section \"Flash the YunoHost image\" above).\n"
msgstr ""

